acing cooler gas entrained in a hot Galactic Fountain outflow. The O\nVII and O VIII absorption observed by Chandra and XMM-Newton may trace the hot\ngas in a highly extended (~100 kpc) Galactic corona or hot gas in the Local\nGroup.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Dec 2004 19:05:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
